<p>In 
 <xref ref-type="fig" rid="polymers-11-00861-f002">Figure 2</xref> the following notations are additionally introduced: 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="mm58">
   <mrow>
    <mrow>
     <msubsup>
      <mstyle mathvariant="bold" mathsize="normal">
       <mi>K</mi>
      </mstyle>
      <mrow/>
      <mi>m</mi>
     </msubsup>
     <mo>=</mo>
     <msubsup>
      <mstyle mathvariant="bold" mathsize="normal">
       <mi>k</mi>
      </mstyle>
      <mn>1</mn>
      <mi>m</mi>
     </msubsup>
     <mo>−</mo>
     <msubsup>
      <mstyle mathvariant="bold" mathsize="normal">
       <mi>k</mi>
      </mstyle>
      <mn>0</mn>
      <mi>m</mi>
     </msubsup>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>–phase gratings’ vectors; 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="mm59">
   <mrow>
    <mrow>
     <msubsup>
      <mstyle mathvariant="bold" mathsize="normal">
       <mi>k</mi>
      </mstyle>
      <mn>0</mn>
      <mi>m</mi>
     </msubsup>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>, 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="mm60">
   <mrow>
    <mrow>
     <msubsup>
      <mstyle mathvariant="bold" mathsize="normal">
       <mi>k</mi>
      </mstyle>
      <mn>1</mn>
      <mi>m</mi>
     </msubsup>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>–wave vectors of the recording beams; 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="mm61">
   <mrow>
    <mrow>
     <msub>
      <mi mathvariant="sans-serif">ϕ</mi>
      <mn>0</mn>
     </msub>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>–the refraction angle of 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="mm62">
   <mrow>
    <mrow>
     <msubsup>
      <mstyle mathvariant="bold" mathsize="normal">
       <mi>k</mi>
      </mstyle>
      <mn>0</mn>
      <mrow/>
     </msubsup>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> beam during its propagation in the medium; as before, 
 <italic>m = o</italic> corresponds to own ordinary wave in the sample, and 
 <italic>m = e</italic> corresponds to own extraordinary wave in the sample.
</p>
